comments: Originally thought to be the voice of a woman or child, it is now known to be the voice of a man, presumably Scott himself, singing the song. As of 2018, this is the earliest known recording of the human voice singing and one of the earliest known recognizable musical recording (a few barely audible experiments from earlier exist). Rather appropriate that the first such recording was, technically, a cover. We have been unable to confirm if this recording has been released commercially in any way, whether digitally, on CD, or in a film or documentary.

name: If I Told You That
comments: Whitney had originally released this as a solo performance in 1998, If I Told You That .  George Michael's vocals were later added and the song was re-mixed for her Greatest Hits album and then later released as a single.  The pair never recorded the song live together, nor did George ever perform or record it solo.
